overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The assistant meticulously
  analyzed the existing codebase against the requirements, identifying key
  missing functionalities. A structured plan was then created and executed to
  address these gaps. The implemented features significantly enhanced the
  questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and user experience, adding a critical
  tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, advanced detection for complex
  sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and valuable
  outbound resources. The data export was also improved to include all collected
  information, and new sections for pain and medical/mental health history were
  integrated to provide a more holistic assessment. The process included
  continuous validation through linting to maintain code quality.
